metadata.name: A Separate Truth
metadata.description: There are different eyes and each of them can see  different truths. But there is no truth. We are the ones who give meaning to everything. We describe the world and create it with our inner dialogue. We are sure of the reality of the world and we never doubt it. When we stop describing and interpreting the world, a gap will be created in our reality and the world will stop. So the truth will not be as we saw it before,
